      <body>
         <div>
            <head>Sample 01: tagsets in taxonomies</head>
            <p>This document demonstrates setting up tagsets by using the mechanism of taxonomy
               declarations in the TEI header.</p>
            <p>One immediate consequence that can be noticed is that feature values must receive
               compound values, the first part of which acts as the namespace, hence "STTS" or "UD",
               etc. as the prefix.</p>
            <p>Another important consequence is that, since feature values are set up as IDs, they
               have to obey XML restrictions on IDs, and in particular, they may not contain commas
               or brackets -- compare the last symbols for punctuation in STTS, where I needed to
               use the full names ("sttsInternalPunctuation" instead of "$("). Farewell short
               tags...</p>
            <p>As far as the category level of tagset definition is concerned, it offers only
               limited documentation options, basically via <gi>desc</gi> . <gi>catDesc</gi> is not
               allowed if the <gi>equiv</gi> elements are to be used. Note by the way that adding
                  <gi>catDesc</gi> to the <ident type="class">att.datcat</ident> class, and then it
               could use the <att>datcat</att> attribute (an issue debated for this class of
               elements back in 2012).</p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Examples of inline annotation</head>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
               <p>
                  <s corresp="https://jenkins-paderborn.tei-c.org/view/LingSIG/job/TEIP5-LingSIG-deadISOCat/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/P5/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/AI.html#index-egXML-d54e130084">
                     <w pos="PPER" lemma="wir"
                        msd="pers:subst:p1:nom:pl">Wir</w>
                     <w pos="VVFIN" lemma="fahren"
                        msd="p1:pl:pres:ind">fahren</w>
                     <w pos="APPR" lemma="in" msd="--">in</w>
                     <w pos="ART" lemma="d"
                        msd="def:acc:sg:masc">den</w>
                     <w pos="NN" lemma="Urlaub"
                        msd="acc:sg:masc">Urlaub</w>
                     <pc pos="$." lemma="." msd="--" join="left">.</pc>
                  </s>
               </p>
            </egXML>
            
